problem_question: A train leaves a station at 72 km/h. Two hours later, a faster train leaves the same station at 88.4 km/h. How long after the faster train departs will it overtake the slower one?
full_response: <answer1>Let me solve this step by step.  When the faster train departs, the slower train has already traveled for 2 hours at 72 km/h. Distance covered by slower train = 72 × 2 = 144 km  Let t = time (in hours) after the faster train departs when it overtakes the slower train.  At the moment of overtaking: - Distance traveled by slower train = 144 + 72t - Distance traveled by faster train = 88.4t  Setting them equal: 144 + 72t = 88.4t 144 = 88.4t - 72t 144 = 16.4t t = 144/16.4 = 8.78048780487804878048780487804878048780487804878048780487804878048780</answer1>  <answer2>yes</answer2>
